Combined from original report via Public Web #2206C-0003-NP: Zoning violation-Above ground swimming pool installed without a permit and fence or barrier. The pool contains more than 5100 gallons of water, and the water depth is above 30 inches. The pool is not being drained into a sanitary sewer. The pool is located in the backyard where construction/modification is being conducted in the basement and cars are constantly parked in the backyard, transpassing neighbors' area. All these activities are being done without a permit being displayed for the community. Children from neighbors are being exposed to unsafety activities coming from this address.

I informed them they needed a permit.  I called Anthony at Landes 540-434-5988 and it was an emergency install due to no A/C and that Landes was aware of the need for permit but they hadn't sent it to our office yet.
